Justice Malala suggests that if "the poor start acting on the belief that the system is rigged, we are all toast" (At Home & Abroad, March 21). When minibus taxi drivers choose, every day of the year, to overtake in the emergency lane — or into oncoming traffic in the turning lane — it’s no different from "tenderpreneurs", parastatal managers and our politicians pulling a quick one on the rest of us. Yet we’ve long resigned ourselves to the fact that such is the way of the road in SA. Rolf EndresCraighall Park The FM welcomes concise letters from readers. They can be sent to fmmail@fm.co.za